Bootstrap script that builds the CTX tooling repo's binaries and copies them into this project's `target/debug/`, so Claude Code hooks and CLAUDE.md (which invoke tools by that fixed path) work in a freshly copied project.

Locates the CTX tooling repo via arg 1, else `$CTX_REPO`, else defaults to `../CTX`; fails fast if `crates/ctx-context/Cargo.toml` isn't found there, meaning it's the wrong repo. Builds via `cargo build -p <pkg>...` for each of `PACKAGES=(ctx-context ctx-scan ctx-verify ctx-cage ctx-summarize ctx-brief)`, then copies `BINARIES=(ctx-context ctx-scan ctx-verify ctx-cage ctx-run ctx-summarize ctx-brief)` — note `ctx-cage`'s package emits two binaries (`ctx-cage` and `ctx-run`), so PACKAGES and BINARIES intentionally have different lengths/entries and must be kept in sync by hand if new dual-binary crates are added.

Only installs binaries — does not sync the `./prompts` files that ctx-scan/ctx-summarize/ctx-brief read at runtime (cwd-relative); that's `scripts/update-template.sh`'s job, and must be run separately. Idempotent/always overwrites: re-run after copying `template/` and whenever the CTX tooling repo updates.